<item>
            <title>[HBASE-65] Thrift Server should have an option to bind to ip address</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-65</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Thrift server can be bound to a port by calling&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;./bin/hbase thrift --port PORT&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As in all other server in hadoop everything is option to bind to a set ip address this will help with security issues&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;example &lt;br/&gt;
./bin/hbase rest --bind 0.0.0.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As of now thrift is on all ip&apos;s on the server making it a security risk. so it would be nice to have the option to bind to a ip so we can limit access to the server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
