                            <comment id="12560013" author="nospmisdivad" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2008 17:58:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good idea... I think this would first require patching the Thrift java runtime so that TServerSocket() could be bound to a specific IP.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12785102" author="lars_francke" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2009 01:03:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I can do this as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1744&quot; title=&quot;Thrift server to match the new java api.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1744&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1744&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Thrift has been modified to accept an InetSocketAddress.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12785180" author="stack" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2009 04:52:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hot dog!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12803022" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2010 22:13:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1360&quot; title=&quot;move up to Thrift 0.2.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1360&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1360&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Assigned to Lars Francke since he did the work over in hbase-1360)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12803132" author="stack" created="Thu, 21 Jan 2010 02:20:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was wrong that hbase-1360 fixed this issue.  HBase-1373 does.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
